The paper discusses a model that combines deep neural networks with tree/forest-based models for efficient serving. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), computer vision (cs.CV), natural language processing (cs.CL), or artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Among these, machine learning (cs.LG) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on the development of a new model that combines deep learning with tree/forest-based models. Information retrieval (cs.IR) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of the proposed model for sponsored search. Computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) are less likely as the paper does not explicitly mention these fields, but they cannot be completely ruled out as the proposed model could potentially be applied to these areas as well. Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is also a possible category as the paper discusses the use of deep learning and tree/forest-based models for efficient serving, which is a common problem in many AI applications.
